Read in data

sh = read_excel("2022SH_covid19.xlsx")
sh$positive = as.numeric(sh$positive)
sh$total = as.numeric(sh$total)
sh$`Asymptomatic infections` = as.numeric(sh$`Asymptomatic infections`)
sh$`pos/total` = as.numeric(sh$`pos/total`)

All data captured from Shanghai gov website （http://wsjkw.sh.gov.cn/yqtb/index.html）. 所有数据均来自于上海市卫生健康委员会网站：http://wsjkw.sh.gov.cn/yqtb/index.html。

p1 = ggplot(data=sh,aes(x=date,y=total)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth() +
  theme_bw() +
  ggtitle("daily total cases") +
  ylab("total (comfirmed + Asymptomatic infections)")

p2 = ggplot(data=sh,aes(x=date,y=total)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth() +
  theme_bw() +
  scale_y_continuous(trans = log10_trans(),
    breaks = trans_breaks("log10", function(x) 10^x),
    labels = trans_format("log10", math_format(10^.x))) +
  ggtitle("daily total cases in log10 scale") +
  ylab("total (comfirmed + Asymptomatic infections)")

ggarrange(p1, p2 , 
          #labels = c("Shanghai daily reported positive cases since Feb 24th", "Shanghai daily reported positive cases since Feb 24th in log10 scale"),
          ncol = 2)

Shanghai daily cases plots, left panel in usual y axis, right panel in log10 scale y axis. Blue line is ggplot automatically generated smooth trend lines, grey is 95% confident interval.

上图为上海市每日新增人数（为确诊和阳性无症状人数之和），左图为正常坐标，右图为将新增人数进行log10转换后得到。 蓝线为绘图包自动拟合的趋势线，灰色为95%置信区间。

ggplot(data=sh,aes(x=date,y=`pos/total`)) +

Plot of ration of daily comfirmed cases to total cases (comfirmed + asymptomatic infections). Y axis in percentage.

每日确诊人数占总数（确诊+阳性无症状）的百分比图。

Fitting data start from March 6th

Fit exponential increase model

Using daily total cases (from March 4th) to fit a exponential increase model. 用从3月4日开始的每日确诊总数进行一个指数上升函数的拟合。

sh$num_date = as.numeric(sh$date) - as.numeric(sh$date)[1]
sh = as.data.frame(sh)
sh$num_date = sh$num_date/(24*3600)
sh_exp <- nls(data=sh[10:44,], total ~ a*exp(b*num_date) + c, 
               start = list(a = 0.5, b = 0.2,c=0.1))
#sh_exp_predict = cbind.data.frame(c(0:32)+10,as.data.frame(predict(sh_exp,x=c(0,50))))

sh_exp_predict <- cbind.data.frame(10:50,coef(sh_exp)[1]*exp(coef(sh_exp)[2]*10:50)+coef(sh_exp)[3])
colnames(sh_exp_predict) = c("date","pre")

##Fit logistic model Using daily total cases (from March 6th) to fit a logistic increase model. 用从3月6日开始的每日确诊总数进行一个logistic函数的拟合。

sh_log <- nls(total ~ SSlogis(num_date, Asym, xmid, scal), data = sh[10:44,])
#sh_log_predict = cbind.data.frame(c(0:32)+10,as.data.frame(predict(sh_log,x=c(0,50))))

sh_log_predict <- cbind.data.frame(10:50,coef(sh_log)[1]/(1+exp((coef(sh_log)[2]- c(10:50))/coef(sh_log)[3])))

colnames(sh_log_predict) = c("date","pre")

Plot fitting results

eq_exp = substitute(italic(y) == a%.%e^(b%.%x)+c, 
         list(a = format(unname(coef(sh_exp)[1]), digits = 2),
              b = format(unname(coef(sh_exp)[2]), digits = 2),
              c = format(unname(coef(sh_exp)[3]), digits = 2)))

eq_exp = as.character(as.expression(eq_exp))
eq_log = substitute(italic(y) == a%/%(1+e^(b-x)%/%c), 
         list(a = format(unname(coef(sh_log)[1]), digits = 2),
              b = format(unname(coef(sh_log)[2]), digits = 2),
              c = format(unname(coef(sh_log)[3]), digits = 2)))

eq_log = as.character(as.expression(eq_log))
Sys.setenv(TZ='UTC')
sh_exp_predict$realdate = as.Date(sh_exp_predict$date, origin = "2022-02-24 UTC")
sh_exp_predict$realdate = as.POSIXct(sh_exp_predict$realdate)
sh_log_predict$realdate = as.Date(sh_log_predict$date, origin = "2022-02-24 UTC")
sh_log_predict$realdate = as.POSIXct(sh_log_predict$realdate)

ggplot(data=sh,aes(x=date,y=total)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(data=sh_exp_predict,aes(x=realdate,y=pre,col="exponential increase")) +
  annotate('text', x = as.POSIXct("2022-04-01 UTC"), y = 60000, label=eq_exp,parse = TRUE,size=4,col="#F8766D")+
  geom_line(data=sh_log_predict,aes(x=realdate,y=pre,col="logistic")) +
  annotate('text', x = as.POSIXct("2022-03-20 UTC"), y = 20000, label=eq_log,parse = TRUE,size=4,col="#00BFC4") +
  theme_bw() +
  xlab("date") +
  ylab("total (comfirmed + Asymptomatic infections)") +
  ggtitle("Fitted data with exponential increase and logistic model\nfitting start from March 6th")

Black dots represent real reported data, red line represents exponential increase equation fitted curve, cyan line represents logistic growth fitted curve.

黑色的点表示实际获取的数据，红色的线表示指数上升模型的趋势，青色的线表示logistic模型的趋势。

Fitting data start from March 13th

Fit logistic

Using daily total cases (from March 6th) to fit a logistic increase model. 用从3月25日开始的每日确诊总数进行一个logistic函数的拟合。

sh_log1 <- nls(total ~ SSlogis(num_date, Asym, xmid, scal), data = sh[30:44,])
sh_log_predict1 <- cbind.data.frame(30:50,coef(sh_log)[1]/(1+exp((coef(sh_log)[2]- c(30:50))/coef(sh_log)[3])))

colnames(sh_log_predict1) = c("date","pre")

Plot fitting results

eq_log1 = substitute(italic(y) == a%/%(1+e^(b-x)%/%c), 
         list(a = format(unname(coef(sh_log1)[1]), digits = 2),
              b = format(unname(coef(sh_log1)[2]), digits = 2),
              c = format(unname(coef(sh_log1)[3]), digits = 2)))

eq_log1 = as.character(as.expression(eq_log1))
Sys.setenv(TZ='UTC')
sh_log_predict1$realdate = as.Date(sh_log_predict1$date, origin = "2022-02-24 UTC")
sh_log_predict1$realdate = as.POSIXct(sh_log_predict1$realdate)

ggplot(data=sh,aes(x=date,y=total)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line(data=sh_log_predict1,aes(x=realdate,y=pre,col="logistic model\nstart from March 25th"),size=2,alpha=0.5) +
  geom_line(data=sh_log_predict,aes(x=realdate,y=pre,col="logistic model\nstart from March 6th"),size=2,alpha=0.5) +
  annotate('text', x = as.POSIXct("2022-03-20 UTC"), y = 40000, label=eq_log1,parse = TRUE,size=4,col="#F8766D") +
  annotate('text', x = as.POSIXct("2022-03-20 UTC"), y = 20000, label=eq_log,parse = TRUE,size=4,col="#00BFC4") +
  theme_bw() +
  xlab("date") +
  ylab("total (comfirmed + Asymptomatic infections)") +
  ggtitle("Fitted data with exponential increase and logistic model\nfitting start from March 25th")

Changing fitting data range does not change logistic model much, maybe because the exponential phase is important and decided the key parameters’ range.

改变logistic 模型的数据拟合范围，并未给最终的模型走势带来巨大的改变。两条线机会完全重合。这可能是由于指数增长阶段对整个模型的数值产生了决定性的作用。
